s. Set in the environmental context of the colonial port city, Dockside Reading explores how imperialism colonizes water. Hofmeyr examines this theme through the concept of hydrocolonialism, which puts together land and sea, empire and environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBooks and readingzGreat BritainxColonies. 0aCensorshipzGreat BritainxColonies. 0aCopyrightzGreat BritainxColonies. 0aCustomhouseszGreat BritainxColonies. 0aCustoms inspectionzGreat BritainxColonies. 0aMarks of originxSocial aspects. 0aPostcolonialism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021 Englishz978311075411708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021z9783110753882oZDB-23-DSP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147802236740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022367/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075411-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DSPb2021